Bombardier profit drops as aircraft deliveries and orders decline
Bombardier Inc., a Canadian aircraft and rail manufacturer, reported a 15 percent drop in net profit on Thursday, under pressure from lower orders and aircraft deliveries in the third quarter and contract issues in its Trains division.
Montreal-based Bombardier has also failed to provide flight test data for its all-new CSeries aircraft or information on whether the aircraft will meet its ambitious timetable for commercial commissioning before next September.
